checkFixity(List<Fixity>, String) - Method in interface com.exlibris.digitool.common.storage.StoragePlugin
Calculates the fixities and checks that the file fixity hasn't changed.
The check is made against the union of the fixities list and the fixities the plugin implementation supports, for example: if the list contains SHA1 and MD5 but the plugin supports only MD5, than the SHA1 entry would be ignored.

getMD(String, String, String, String, String) - Method in interface com.exlibris.digitool.repository.ifc.IEWebServices
API for getting the MD of an IE , REP or File, Only MD on entity level (which is in Permanent) is returned.
The ID of the source MD section is the mid (saved in Rosetta DB)
No parameters - return all PID's MDs
MID - return matching MD (ignore type, subtype if provided)
type (only) - return all matching for type
type+subType - return all matching for type+subtype
subType (only) - not supported
type+subType mismatch - error

Supported type:subType pairs:
descriptive: dc
source: marc, dc, mods, text_md, image_niso,video_md, audio_md, copyrights, rights, other, ead, OTHER:article
mets_section: structMap

A better way to access a file: If the storageId & storedEntityIdentifier are present, use them with the StoragePlugin, otherwise use the filePath directly.
The filePath method is disencouraged, use it only when storageId & storedEntityIdentifier are empty.
File path may be null if storageId & storedEntityIdentifier are present.
